      "text": "In software engineering, a project fork happens when developers take a copy of source code from one software package and start independent development on it, creating a distinct and separate piece of software. The term often implies not merely a development branch, but a split in the developer community, a form of schism - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fork_(software_development) wikipedia]"
    },
